@ENDNODE

@NODE ApplicationLoad "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Application.Load -- load program configuration (V1.7)

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        mui.DoMethod(id, "Load", name$)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        @{"Application.Save" LINK ApplicationSave}, Application.Load and @{"Notify.ExportID" LINK NotifyExportID} offer an easy
        way of saving and loading a program's configuration.

        Each gadget with a @{"Notify.ExportID" LINK NotifyExportID} will get its contents saved during
        @{"Application.Save" LINK ApplicationSave} and restored during Application.Load. This makes it
        very easy to design a configuration window with "Save", "Use" and
        "Cancel" buttons to allow the user storing the settings. When the
        application starts, you would just have to call Application.Load and the
        stored settings will be read and installed.

        The "name$" parameter must be set to the name of the file you wish to
        load the settings from. Usually you won't need to think of a real name
        but instead use one of the following special values:

        ::ENV     Load settings from ENV:.

        ::ENVARC  Load settings from ENVARC:.

        Not all classes are able to import and export their contents. Currently,
        you may define a @{"Notify.ExportID" LINK NotifyExportID} for

        String class
                  @{"String.Contents" LINK StringContents} is ex/imported.

        Radio class
                  @{"Radio.Active" LINK RadioActive} is ex/imported.

        Cycle class
                  @{"Cycle.Active" LINK CycleActive} is ex/imported.

        Listview class
                  @{"Listview.Active" LINK ListviewActive} is /ex/imported.

        Text class
                  @{"Text.Contents" LINK TextContents} is ex/imported.

        Slider class
                  @{"Slider.Level" LINK SliderLevel} is ex/imported.

        Area class
                  @{"Area.Selected" LINK AreaSelected} is ex/imported (e.g. for Checkmark gadgets)

        Menuitem class
                  @{"Menuitem.Selected" LINK MenuitemSelected} is ex/imported.

        Group class
                  @{"Group.ActivePage" LINK GroupActivePage} is ex/imported.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the application object
        name$     name of the file you wish to load the settings from or special
                  value (see above)

@ENDNODE

