        ISG

@ENDNODE

@NODE Button "MUI Royale Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Button class allows you to create buttons very easily. If the button label
    contains an underscore, MUI Royale will automatically set up the character
    following this underscore as a keyboard shortcut. If you don't want this
    behaviour, set @{"Button.NoAutoKey" LINK ButtonNoAutoKey} to TRUE.

    Example:

        <button id="ok" notify="pressed">OK</button>

    The button name you specify here can use text formatting codes. See @{"Text" LINK TextFormat}
    @{"formatting codes" LINK TextFormat} for details.

    @{"Button.HiChar                     " LINK ButtonHiChar} Highlight a character in button label
    @{"Button.Label                      " LINK ButtonLabel} Set/get button label
    @{"Button.NoAutoKey                  " LINK ButtonNoAutoKey} Disable auto button shortcut
    @{"Button.Pressed                    " LINK ButtonPressed} Learn if a button is pressed
    @{"Button.Selected                   " LINK ButtonSelected} Toggle selection state
    @{"Button.Toggle                     " LINK ButtonToggle} Create toggle button
@ENDNODE

@NODE ButtonHiChar "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Button.HiChar -- highlight a character in button label

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        If the character given here exists in the displayed string (no matter if
        upper or lower case), it will be underlined. Highlighting a character in
        the button label is useful in connection with @{"Area.ControlChar" LINK AreaControlChar}.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
