@NODE Group "MUI Royale Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Group class is responsible for the complete layout of a MUI window. A group
    may contain any number of child objects, maybe buttons, cycle gadgets or
    even other groups.

    Some attributes of group class define how the children of a group are
    layouted. You can e.g. tell your group to place its children horizontally
    (in a row) or vertically (in a column). Since every MUI object knows about
    its minimum and maximum dimensions, group class has everything it needs to
    do that job.

    More sophisticated layout is possible by assigning different weights to
    objects in a group or by making a group two-dimensional.

    Beneath the layout issues, a group object passes attributes and methods
    through to all of its children. Thus, you can talk and listen to any child
    of a group by talking and listening to the group itself.

    The following different group types are supported by MUI Royale:

    <hgroup>  Group children will be laid out in a row (vertical).

    <vgroup>  Group children will be laid out in a column (horizontal).

    <colgroup>
              Group children will be laid out in columns.

    <virtgroup>
              A virtual group. Normally used inside a scrollgroup. See @{"Virtgroup" LINK Virtgroup}
              @{"class" LINK Virtgroup} for details.

    <scrollgroup>
              A group with scrollbars. Virtual groups are usually embedded
              inside a scrollgroup. See @{"Scrollgroup class" LINK Scrollgroup} for details.

    Column groups are useful if you need to have identical gadget sizes for all
    your children in a group for a more pleasant visual appearance. For example,
    imagine a form made up of string gadgets and text objects. It is recommended
    to use a <colgroup> here because it leads to a clear and ordered visual
    appearance. Here's an example:

        <colgroup columns="2">
           <text>Name</text>
           <string/>
           <text>Street</text>
           <string/>
           <text>City</text>
           <string/>
           <text>Zip code</text>
           <string/>
           <text>Country</text>
           <string/>
           <text>Telephone</text>
           <string/>
           <text>Email</text>
           <string/>
        </colgroup>

    If we used a <vgroup> with one <hgroup> per row the appearance would be
    pretty bad because the string gadget's width would be different for each
    line which looks pretty non-professional.

    @{"Group.ActivePage                  " LINK GroupActivePage} Set/get active page of page group
    @{"Group.AddHead                     " LINK GroupAddHead} Add detached object as first group child
    @{"Group.AddTail                     " LINK GroupAddTail} Add detached object as last group child
    @{"Group.ChildList                   " LINK GroupChildList} Get a list of all group children
    @{"Group.Columns                     " LINK GroupColumns} Define group columns
    @{"Group.ExitChange                  " LINK GroupExitChange} Terminate group modification state
    @{"Group.HorizSpacing                " LINK GroupHorizSpacing} Set/get horizontal spacing
    @{"Group.InitChange                  " LINK GroupInitChange} Prepare group addition or removal of children
    @{"Group.Insert                      " LINK GroupInsert} Insert detached object after specified child
    @{"Group.PageMode                    " LINK GroupPageMode} Put group in page mode
    @{"Group.Remove                      " LINK GroupRemove} Detach child from group
    @{"Group.SameHeight                  " LINK GroupSameHeight} Set same height for all children
    @{"Group.SameSize                    " LINK GroupSameSize} Set same size for all children
    @{"Group.SameWidth                   " LINK GroupSameWidth} Set same width for all children
    @{"Group.Spacing                     " LINK GroupSpacing} Set/get spacing
    @{"Group.Title                       " LINK GroupTitle} Set group title
    @{"Group.VertSpacing                 " LINK GroupVertSpacing} Set/get vertical spacing
@ENDNODE

@NODE GroupActivePage "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Group.ActivePage -- set/get active page of page group

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Set (or get) the active page of a page group. Only this active page is
        displayed, all others are hidden.

        The value may range from 0 (for the first child) to numchildren-1 (for
        the last child). Children are adressed in the order of creation.

        The following special values are possible when setting the active page:

        First     First page.

        Last      Last page.

        Prev      Previous page.

        Next      Next page.

        Advance   Advance page.

