@NODE GroupChildList "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Group.ChildList -- get a list of all group children (V1.2)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This attribute allows you to get a table that contains information about
        all children that are currently attached the group. For each child in
        the group, the following table elements will be initialized:

        ID:       Contains the ID of the group child.

        Class:    Contains the name of the class this object belongs to, e.g.
                  "Cycle".

        MUIClass: Contains the internal MUI class name for this object, e.g.
                  "Cycle.mui". This is probably of not much interest for your
                  application.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Table

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        G

   @{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}
        t = mui.Get("mygroup", "childlist")
