@NODE ListviewInsert "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Listview.Insert -- insert new entry

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        mui.DoMethod(id, "Insert", pos, column1$, ...)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Insert one new entry into a list. If the listview has multiple columns,
        you need to pass as many arguments as there are columns in the listview.

        The insert position is specified in the "pos" argument. The new entry
        will be added in front of the entry specified by "pos". This can be an
        absolute index position starting at 0 for the first entry or one of the
        following special values:

        Top       Insert as first entry.

        Active    Insert in front of the active entry.

        Sorted    Insert sorted.

        Bottom    Insert as last entry.

        If "pos" is bigger or equal to the number of entries in the list, it's
        treated like Bottom.

        All entries you insert using this method can use text formatting codes.
        See @{"Text formatting codes" LINK TextFormat} for details.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the listview object
        pos       insert position as absolute number or special value (see
                  above)
        column1$  entry to insert into first column
        ...       more entries if listview has multiple columns

@ENDNODE

@NODE ListviewInsertPosition "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Listview.InsertPosition -- query position of newly inserted entry

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
