@NODE ListviewJump "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Listview.Jump -- scroll to an entry

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        mui.DoMethod(id, "Jump", pos)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Scroll any entry into the visible part of a list.

        Note: Jumping to an entry doesn't mean to make this entry the active
        one. This can be done by setting the @{"Listview.Active" LINK ListviewActive} attribute.

        Starting with MUI Royale 1.4, "pos" can also be one of the following
        special values:

        Active    Jump to active item.

        Top       Jump to top.

        Bottom    Jump to bottom.

        Up        Jump one page up.

        Down      Jump one page down.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the listview object
        pos       number of the entry that should be made visible. Pass "Active"
                  to jump to the active entry.

