@NODE Listviewcolumn "MUI Royale Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Listviewcolumn class is needed when creating listviews. It allows you to
    specify different attributes for the columns of your listviews.

    Listviewcolumn class must always be embedded inside a <listview>
    declaration. See @{"Listview class" LINK Listview} for details.

    @{"Listviewcolumn.Bar                " LINK ListviewcolumnBar} Use separator bar between columns
    @{"Listviewcolumn.Col                " LINK ListviewcolumnCol} Set column order
    @{"Listviewcolumn.Delta              " LINK ListviewcolumnDelta} Set column width
    @{"Listviewcolumn.Hidden             " LINK ListviewcolumnHidden} Show/hide listview columns
    @{"Listviewcolumn.MinWidth           " LINK ListviewcolumnMinWidth} Set minimum column width
    @{"Listviewcolumn.MaxWidth           " LINK ListviewcolumnMaxWidth} Set maximum column width
    @{"Listviewcolumn.PreParse           " LINK ListviewcolumnPreParse} Set preparse text string for column
    @{"Listviewcolumn.Title              " LINK ListviewcolumnTitle} Set column title
    @{"Listviewcolumn.Weight             " LINK ListviewcolumnWeight} Set column weight
@ENDNODE

@NODE ListviewcolumnBar "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Listviewcolumn.Bar -- use separator bar between columns

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
