@NODE Poplist "MUI Royale Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Poplist class simplifies creation of popups that contain just a simple list
    of predefined gadget contents. Poplist class will create a string gadget and
    a popup button for you. Whenever the user hits the popup button, a window
    containing a list of predefined entries will be opened so that the user can
    choose one from the list.

    When creating a poplist object, you have to use the <item> tag to fill it
    with entries. Here is an example:

        <poplist>
           <item>The</item>
           <item>quick</item>
           <item>brown</item>
           <item>fox</item>
           <item>jumps</item>
           <item>over</item>
           <item>the</item>
           <item>lazy</item>
           <item>dog</item>
        </poplist>

    The list entries that you specify using the <item> tag can use text
    formatting codes. See @{"Text formatting codes" LINK TextFormat} for details.

    @{"Poplist.Acknowledge               " LINK PoplistAcknowledge} Get notified when the user hits RETURN
    @{"Poplist.AdvanceOnCR               " LINK PoplistAdvanceOnCR} Activate next object in cycle chain
    @{"Poplist.Contents                  " LINK PoplistContents} Set/get current poplist contents
