@NODE Register "MUI Royale Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Register class is a special class for handling multi page groups. Using this
    class, you only have to supply an array of groups, describing the register's
    children. How these children are visualized, either with a cycle gadget of
    with a register-like group, is the choice of the user. You need to use the
    @{"Group.Title" LINK GroupTitle} attribute to give your register tabs titles.

    Here is an example of a three page register group:

        <register>
           <vgroup title="Page 1">
               <listview>
                  <column>
                     <item>Entry</item>
                  </column>
               </listview>
           </vgroup>
           <vgroup title="Page 2">
               <texteditor/>
           </vgroup>
           <vgroup title="Page 3">
               <button>Click me</button>
           </vgroup>
        </register>

    @{"Register.ActivePage               " LINK RegisterActivePage} Set/get active page of register group
    @{"Register.AddPage                  " LINK RegisterAddPage} Add new page to register group
    @{"Register.Closable                 " LINK RegisterClosable} Add close gadget to register pages
    @{"Register.ClosePage                " LINK RegisterClosePage} Remove page from register group
    @{"Register.CloseRequest             " LINK RegisterCloseRequest} Handle close request of page
    @{"Register.GetPageID                " LINK RegisterGetPageID} Return ID of a page inside the register group
    @{"Register.InsertPage               " LINK RegisterInsertPage} Insert new page into register group
    @{"Register.Pages                    " LINK RegisterPages} Find out number of pages in register
    @{"Register.Position                 " LINK RegisterPosition} Set position of page tabs
@ENDNODE

@NODE RegisterActivePage "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Register.ActivePage -- set/get active page of register group

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Set (or get) the active page of a register group. Only this active page
        is displayed, all others are hidden.

        The value may range from 0 (for the first child) to numchildren-1 (for
        the last child). Children are adressed in the order of creation.

        The following special values are possible when setting the active page:

        First     First page.

        Last      Last page.

        Prev      Previous page.

        Next      Next page.

        Advance   Advance page.

        Note: You may *never* supply an incorrect page value!

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Number or string (see above for possible values)

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        ISGN

@ENDNODE

@NODE RegisterAddPage "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Register.AddPage -- add new page to register (V1.2)

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        mui.DoMethod(id, "AddPage", obj)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This method can be used to add a new page to a register group. The new
        page specified by "obj" must be a detached group object. This detached
        group object will then be added as the register's last page. After this
        method returns the specified group object will change its state from
        detached to attached. That is why you must no longer use functions that
        expect a detached object with this object now.

        Detached MUI objects can be created either by calling the
        @{"mui.CreateObject()" LINK muiCreateObject} function or by explicitly detaching them from their
        parent by using the @{"Register.ClosePage" LINK RegisterClosePage} method.

        This feature requires at least MUI 4.0.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the register object
        obj       id of the group object to add as a new page

@ENDNODE

@NODE RegisterClosable "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Register.Closable -- add close gadget to register pages (V1.2)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        If you set this attribute to TRUE, MUI will add close gadgets to each
        individual tab page. When the user hits the close gadget,
        @{"Register.CloseRequest" LINK RegisterCloseRequest} will trigger.

        This feature requires at least MUI 4.0.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Boolean

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        I

@ENDNODE

@NODE RegisterClosePage "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Register.ClosePage -- remove page from register group (V1.2)

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        mui.DoMethod(id, "ClosePage", obj)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This method will close the page tab specified by "obj". The group object
        that constitutes the page that is being closed will then change its
        state from attached to detached. This means that you could attach it now
        to another register or group using a function like @{"Group.Insert" LINK GroupInsert} and
        @{"Register.AddPage" LINK RegisterAddPage}, respectively, or you could free it using
        @{"mui.FreeObject()" LINK muiFreeObject}.

        This feature requires at least MUI 4.0.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the register object
        obj       id of the page to remove

@ENDNODE

@NODE RegisterCloseRequest "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Register.CloseRequest -- handle close request of page (V1.2)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        When the user hits a register page's close gadget, the page isn't closed
        immediately. Instead MUI only sets this attribute to TRUE to allow your
        application to react.

        Usually, you will setup a notification that automatically closes the
        page when a close request appears, but you could e.g. pop up a
        confirmation requester or do some other things first.

        This feature requires at least MUI 4.0.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Boolean

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        N

@ENDNODE

@NODE RegisterGetPageID "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Register.GetPageID -- return ID of a page inside the register group (V1.2)

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        id$ = mui.DoMethod(id, "GetPageID", idx)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This method returns the ID of the page at the specified index within the
        register group. "idx" can be an absolute number ranging from 0 to the
        number of pages in the register minus 1 or it can be one of the
        following special values:

        First     First page.

        Last      Last page.

        Active    Active page.

        This feature requires at least MUI 4.0.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the register object
        idx       absolute index of desired page or special string constant (see
                  above)

   @{b}RESULTS@{ub}
        id$       id of the page object at the specified register index

@ENDNODE

@NODE RegisterInsertPage "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Register.InsertPage -- insert new page into register (V1.4)

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        mui.DoMethod(id, "InsertPage", obj, pos)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This method can be used to insert a new page into a register group. The
        new page specified by "obj" must be a detached group object. This
        detached group object will then be inserted into the register position
        specified by "pos". This is an integer position starting from 0 for the
        first page. After this method returns the specified group object will
        change its state from detached to attached. That is why you must no
        longer use functions that expect a detached object with this object now.

        Detached MUI objects can be created either by calling the
        @{"mui.CreateObject()" LINK muiCreateObject} function or by explicitly detaching them from their
        parent by using the @{"Register.ClosePage" LINK RegisterClosePage} method.

        This feature requires at least MUI 4.0.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the register object
        obj       id of the group object to insert as a new page
        pos       insertion position starting from 0 for the first page

@ENDNODE

@NODE RegisterPages "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Register.Pages -- find out number of pages in register (V1.2)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
