        I

@ENDNODE

@NODE Slider "MUI Royale Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    The slider class generates a GUI element that allows a user to adjust a
    numeric value. The programmer doesn't have very much influence on the
    slider's outfit, there are only very few tags available. Future versions of
    MUI will probably include some preferences options to allow the user (*not*
    the programmer) to configure this outfit.

    Note that since slider is a subclass of group class, you can get horizontal
    or vertical sliders by simply using the @{"Slider.Horiz" LINK SliderHoriz} attribute. Default is a
    horizontal slider.

    Here is an XML example of a slider that allows the user to configure a
    number ranging from 0 to 100:

        <slider min="0" max="100"/>

    @{"Slider.Format                     " LINK SliderFormat} Customize slider text
    @{"Slider.Horiz                      " LINK SliderHoriz} Set/get alignment of slider
    @{"Slider.Level                      " LINK SliderLevel} Set/get current slider level
    @{"Slider.Max                        " LINK SliderMax} Set/get maximum level of slider
    @{"Slider.Min                        " LINK SliderMin} Set/get minimum level of slider
    @{"Slider.Pressed                    " LINK SliderPressed} Learn when slider knob is pressed
    @{"Slider.Quiet                      " LINK SliderQuiet} Hide current level from slider
    @{"Slider.Reverse                    " LINK SliderReverse} Reverse direction of slider
    @{"Slider.Stringify                  " LINK SliderStringify} Setup callback for custom slider text
@ENDNODE

@NODE SliderFormat "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Slider.Format -- customize slider text

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        A template string to describe the format of the slider display. Whenever
        Slider.mui thinks it's time to render a new value, it doesn't simply
        write it to a string but uses the format mask specified in this
        attribute to compose the new string that is then rendered to the slider
        display. Any "%ld" in the format string is replaced by the current
        slider level.

        Note well: The maximum length of the result string for Slider.Format is
        limited to 32 characters. If you need more, you must use
        @{"Slider.Stringify" LINK SliderStringify}.

        Slider.Format defaults to "%ld".

        The string you specify here can use text formatting codes. See @{"Text" LINK TextFormat}
        @{"formatting codes" LINK TextFormat} for details.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        String

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        ISG

   @{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}
        mui.Set(obj, "Format", "Custom text: %ld")

        The code above sets the slider text to "Custom text" followed by the
        current slider level.

@ENDNODE

