@NODE Text "MUI Royale Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Text class allows generating objects that contain some kind of text. You can
    control the outfit of your text with some special control characters,
    including italics, bold, underline and color codes. Format codes align text
    either left, centered or right, linefeeds allow multiline text fields.

    Please note that text class does not offer automatic word wrapping. If you
    want to have on-the-fly word wrapping, you have to use floattext class
    instead. See @{"Floattext" LINK Floattext} for details.

    Here is an example of how to use the <text> command:

        <text>Hello World</text>

    Here is the same example in bold:

        <text>\\33bHello World</text>

    The string you specify here can use text formatting codes. See @{"Text" LINK TextFormat}
    @{"formatting codes" LINK TextFormat} for details.

    @{"Text.Contents                     " LINK TextContents} Set/get text object contents
    @{"Text.HiChar                       " LINK TextHiChar} Highlight single character
    @{"Text.PreParse                     " LINK TextPreParse} Set/get preparse string for text object
    @{"Text.SetMax                       " LINK TextSetMax} Limit maximum width
    @{"Text.SetMin                       " LINK TextSetMin} Set a minimum width for text object
    @{"Text.SetVMax                      " LINK TextSetVMax} Limit object height
@ENDNODE

@NODE TextContents "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Text.Contents -- set/get text object contents

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        String to be displayed in a text object.

        If the string is larger than available display space, it will be
        clipped. Setting Text.Contents to "" results in an empty text object.

        The string you specify here can use text formatting codes. See @{"Text" LINK TextFormat}
        @{"formatting codes" LINK TextFormat} for details.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
