@NODE TexteditorExportHook "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Texteditor.ExportHook -- set text editor's export hook (V1.4)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Depending on the inputs a different export hook will be fired as soon as
        text is exported from the text editor gadget. The default is to export
        the currently shown data as is. That means, that all text, including the
        escape sequences for showing soft styles will be exported.

        You can change this behaviour by setting this attribute. The following
        export hooks are recognized:

        Plain     Export all text as displayed, including escape sequences
                  ('\\33'). This is the default mode.

        EMail     Export all text, but convert the soft-style escape sequences
                  into the pseudo-standard text sequences like:

                      *bold*      : for bold text
                      /italic/    : for italic text
                      _underline_ : for underlined text
                      #colored#   : for colored/highlighted text
                      <tsb>       : for a thick separator bar
                      <sb>        : for a thin separator bar

        NoStyle   Export all text like the "Plain" variant, but strip off all
                  style relevant escape sequences. Also converts the escape
                  sequences for the thick and thin separator bar into <tsb> and
                  <sb> like the "EMail" hook.

        See @{"Texteditor.ImportHook" LINK TexteditorImportHook} for details.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        String (see above for possible values)

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        IS

@ENDNODE

@NODE TexteditorExportWrap "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Texteditor.ExportWrap -- use hard word wrapping

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This attribute allows the built-in export hooks to perform hard word
