@NODE Toolbarbutton "MUI Royale Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Toolbar button class is a subclass of toolbar class. It cannot be used on
    its own but must always be encapsulated inside a toolbar class definition.
    Toolbar button class creates a single button for its super toolbar class.
    Please note that the XML tag for this class is just <button>, not
    <toolbarbutton>. See @{"Toolbar class" LINK Toolbar} for details.

    @{"Toolbarbutton.Disabled            " LINK ToolbarbuttonDisabled} Enable/disable button
    @{"Toolbarbutton.DisImage            " LINK ToolbarbuttonDisImage} Set disabled button image
    @{"Toolbarbutton.Exclude             " LINK ToolbarbuttonExclude} Set exclusion mask
    @{"Toolbarbutton.Hide                " LINK ToolbarbuttonHide} Show/hide button
    @{"Toolbarbutton.Image               " LINK ToolbarbuttonImage} Set button image
    @{"Toolbarbutton.Immediate           " LINK ToolbarbuttonImmediate} Create immediate button
    @{"Toolbarbutton.NoClick             " LINK ToolbarbuttonNoClick} Create a dead button
    @{"Toolbarbutton.Pressed             " LINK ToolbarbuttonPressed} Learn if a button is pressed
    @{"Toolbarbutton.Selected            " LINK ToolbarbuttonSelected} Toggle selection state
    @{"Toolbarbutton.SelImage            " LINK ToolbarbuttonSelImage} Set selected button image
    @{"Toolbarbutton.ShortHelp           " LINK ToolbarbuttonShortHelp} Set short help for toolbar button
    @{"Toolbarbutton.Sleep               " LINK ToolbarbuttonSleep} Create sleeping button
    @{"Toolbarbutton.Toggle              " LINK ToolbarbuttonToggle} Create toggle button
@ENDNODE

