@NODE Window "MUI Royale Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Objects of window class are used to generate windows and supply a place
    where MUI gadgets feel well. It handles the complicated task of window
    resizing fully automatic, you don't need to worry about that.

    Windows are children of an application, you cannot use a window object
    without having a parent application object. On the other side, the gadgets
    in a window are children of the window, you cannot use MUI gadgets without
    having a parent MUI window.

    Creating a window object does not mean to open it instantly. This is done
    later by setting the window's @{"Window.Open" LINK WindowOpen} attribute. If your application has
    several windows, the usual way is to create them all at once at startup time
    and open/close it later just by setting @{"Window.Open" LINK WindowOpen}.

    There is no difference in talking to gadgets whether their parent window is
    open or not. If you e.g. set the contents of a string gadget in an open
    window, the gadget will refresh immediately. If the window is closed, the
    gadget just remembers its new setting and displays it later.

    @{"Window.Activate                   " LINK WindowActivate} Change activation state of window
    @{"Window.ActiveObject               " LINK WindowActiveObject} Set/get active window object
    @{"Window.AppWindow                  " LINK WindowAppWindow} Make window an app window
    @{"Window.Borderless                 " LINK WindowBorderless} Show/hide window border
    @{"Window.CloseGadget                " LINK WindowCloseGadget} Configure window's close gadget
    @{"Window.CloseRequest               " LINK WindowCloseRequest} Handle close request of window
    @{"Window.DefaultObject              " LINK WindowDefaultObject} Set/get window's default object
    @{"Window.DepthGadget                " LINK WindowDepthGadget} Configure window's depth gadget
    @{"Window.DragBar                    " LINK WindowDragBar} Configure window's drag bar
    @{"Window.Height                     " LINK WindowHeight} Set/get window height
    @{"Window.LeftEdge                   " LINK WindowLeftEdge} Set/get left edge of window
    @{"Window.Menustrip                  " LINK WindowMenustrip} Set window's menustrip
    @{"Window.MouseObject                " LINK WindowMouseObject} Find object that mouse is currently over
    @{"Window.MuiID                      " LINK WindowMuiID} Set/get window identifier
    @{"Window.NeedsMouseObject           " LINK WindowNeedsMouseObject} Enable mouse tracking
    @{"Window.NoMenus                    " LINK WindowNoMenus} Disable window menu
